.TH hsh 1 "February 2026" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- a minimal UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple shell created as a project for Holberton School. It reads commands from the standard input and attempts to execute them on the system.

The shell operates in two modes:
.PP
.IP "\fBInteractive Mode\fR"
When the input is connected to a terminal (keyboard), \fBhsh\fR displays a prompt ($) and waits for user input.
.IP "\fBNon-interactive Mode\fR"
When commands are piped into the shell (e.g., echo "ls" | ./hsh), it processes the commands and exits without displaying a prompt.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
Displays a prompt ($ ) if the standard input is a terminal.
.IP \(bu 2
Uses \fBexecve\fR to run programs found in the \fBPATH\fR.
.IP \(bu 2
Handles the end-of-file condition (Ctrl+D) gracefully.
.IP \(bu 2
Supports basic built-in commands like \fBexit\fR and \fBenv\fR.
.IP \(bu 2
Prints clear error messages in the style of \fB/bin/sh\fR.

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on successful execution. If a command is not found, it returns 127.

.SH BUGS
This version does not support pipes, redirections, or command arguments. Only single-word commands are executed.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
\fBhsh\fR uses the system environment variables, specifically \fBPATH\fR to locate executables and \fBenviron\fR for the \fBenv\fR command.

